content.protection: Three bolts, but a standard rack is also needed. Two .5 And #1 BD's are helpful. On the first acent a blue alien was used for first piece, but after cleaning route a .5 fit even better. After the first bolt was added it is the routes second piece. After the last bolt head up and right around courner to finish on Moon Walk.
content.location: This route is right and around the corner from moon lake monster.

content.description: This route goes to the top of cliff. Start left of moon lake monster, on a blocky right trending ramp system. After right diagnoling crack ends head straight up.

content.location: Start up one step for man, then continue up hand crack to left side of ledge. Rap from anchors.

content.description: Fun ramp, will get better as it cleans up.
content.protection: Standard rack, a 000 BD is helpful. 2 bolts protect the start.
content.location: The ramp just right of what lies beneath

content.description: Route is fairly straight forward. After reaching the right diagnaling ramp, head up and right. At top of ramp follow arÃªte left to ledge and double anchors
content.protection: Three bolts protect the start, but a standard rack is needed to complete route.
content.location: After reaching the main wall platform, locate route with three clearly visible bolts. Rappel from chains.

content.description: Belay at a big right side facing flake with thin hands and good protection. Continue up to the right to a ledge short ledge - continue up the right trending fingercrack - good protection but not much feet to place gear. Place protection before topping out. No anchors and a steep scramble after topping out to build a trad anchor.
content.protection: I placed a BD .75, .5, #1, and silver stopper. One more .4 would have protected the crux if you're uncomfortable with finger locks with poor feet.
content.location: Park at the moon lake trail and take the trail 1.5 miles before hitting the second talus field. Continue up the second talus field, keeping the first sandstone cliff to your left. The routes begin to appear after reaching the tree line.
Head up same start as One step for man, but continue straight up broken face. Rappel from slings at tree on top of cliff
